postcontent:
2007 Springfield receiver, all the rest NM military parts.  This was built by a very well-known armorer and good friend who passed away a few years ago.  I have shot one high-power match with it, then cleaned it and stored it in my safe.  It has not been fired since the high-power match but has been oiled and maintained.

It has a NM Douglas barrel, NM sights, and a sweet NRA-legal trigger.  The stock and handguard is from an M14 and has been glassed in where the selector switch used to be.  It has a web sling, TRW bolt, and 2 mil-spec/original magazines included.

I could go on to describe it in more detail, but if you are seriously interested, you will want to know who built it and what he built it with.  This armorer was a very good friend of mine, and was very well known in the CMP/NRA High Power community.  It is legal for matches and/or would make a great hunting/sniper type rifle.  You can't get much better than this...

I will not advertise it with his name - I don't want to capitalize on his name (as others have done).  Again, if you are serious, you can email or text me and I will tell you.

Value between $3500-$5000.  I know that's a very wide range, but if you know and understand the rifle/armorer you will understand why.

postcontent: New unfired direct from the factory Kel Tec KSG 12 shot 12 gauge shot gun in the hard to find OD Green. This is serious fire power. From the factory: The KSG is our first entry into the shotgun market. The size, shape and design are similar to the currently available Kel-Tec RFB rifle, but the KSG ejects downward, instead of forward. The KSG weighs 6.9lbs and is as compact as legally possible with a 26.1" overall length and an 18.5" cylinder bore barrel. Even with this compact size, the internal dual tube magazines hold an impressive 6 rounds of 12 gage 3" shells each, for a total capacity of 6+6+1 (7 per tube if using 2-3/4" shells). The simple and reliable pump action feeds from either the left or right tube. The feed side is manually selected by a lever located behind the trigger guard. The lever can be positioned in the center detent in order to easily clear the chamber without feeding another round from either magazine. A cross bolt style safety blocks the sear, and the pump release lever is located in front of the trigger guard. The pump includes an under Picatinny rail for the mounting of a forward grip, or a light or laser.

title: For Sale:  Custom, Handmade Steel and Knapped Blade Knives with Sheaths
postcontent: I have more than 35 handmade stainless steel and obsidian blade knives with specially treated deer or elk antler handles. The photos picture some of the knives. The vast majority of my steel blade blanks are fabricated from 440c high carbon stainless steel. They are various styles and sizes ranging from 12-inch bowie knife blades to the smallest patch knife. The knapped blade art deco knives feature obsidian, agate and blades flint knapped by master knappers. Both my steel and knapped blades are hafted to elk or deer antler handles that have been specially treated, finely sanded and polished. Some feature hand carved images such as eagles and deer on the handles by nationally known artist by Rob Roberts. The elk antler handles are fitted with exotic wooden end caps. The ends of my deer antler handles feature finely carved, sanded and polished round skull bone on the end of the burr. Some handles have been dyed to enhance their appearance. The tangs of my steel blades have been deeply inserted into the antlers and permanently attached with industrial-strength epoxy. Although I offer a 14-day money-back guarantee, I have never had one returned. My rating as an eBay seller is 100 percent. My knives have been praised on Facebook and in the Other Weapons category of firearmstalk.com many times. Main Street Jewelers in Plattsmouth, Neb., has prominent display case of my knives for sale. Pilchers Indian Store in Omaha, Neb., has a great inventory of my obsidian blade knives which are hafted in the traditional method with sinew; however, the blades also are permanently attached with epoxy. Retail stores in other states also sell my knives. My custom handmade leather sheaths are the highest quality, sold at cost. Prices vary depending upon the knife. Whatever the cost, it will be much less when averaged over the decades than inferior, retail-priced knives. A knife in a store may cost less, but does not have the value of a custom, handmade knife to become an heirloom passed from generation to generation. Many personal referrals available. Various knife collectors have 15 or more Porter Knives and have ordered many more for gifts, including many groomsmen. You may also pick the blade want, and the handle you want (or let me suggest excellent choices) and I'll make a unique, one-of-a-kind knife that can never be duplicated and is valued for its beauty and craftsmanship.

It is a Tapco G2, but when you feel it and shoot it you will clearly feel how clean it is. The action is extremely smooth and all of the rivets are perfect. The Brake really attracts attention at the range with it's huge fireballs. The sights are dead on, and there is no cant what-so-ever. This is not a Garage build, and it was put together extremely well. I have shot this rifle out to 300M with consistent and accurate hits, and it has not once had a malfunction of any type. I have Exactly 300 rounds through it (60 rounds of Winchester FMJ, the Rest were Wolf, Uly, and Tula FMJ and HP Non-corrosive). I have not bump fired it or any stupid shit like that. title: For Sale:  Springfield Omega 6" Long Slide 45 Multi-Caliber
postcontent: This was like other Springfield Armory Omegas had the frame from the U.S. and the slide made in Germany. Previous owner bought this gun in 1992 while working in Germany. The design of the slide is from Joe Peters of Peters Stahl, (Peters' Steel Manufacturing). KPS the German manufacturer, was the name of the Peters Stahl company for a short while. The Peters Stahl 1911 family of pistols are among the finest 1911s money can buy. They started manufacturing their range of custom guns in the mid-1980s and are still around today. the founder Joe Peters went on to Form KPS, who manufactured this pistol. Along with excellent build quality (this gun is build like a tank!), the main difference from ordinary 1911s is that the Peters Stahl guns use a Sig type lock up, where the breach locks directly into the ejection port. Basically this means that you are combining the two most reliable and accurate major caliber semi-automatic pistol formats – Colt/ Browning and Sig. The result is a pistol that is utterly reliable and accurate. The fact that it is a .45 ACP with a six inch barrel just makes it even better. The double extraction system is designed to be "Multicaliber" with an adjustment screw on the slide. This allows the breech face to be altered to fit the cartridge being fired. To convert to any caliber (.45, 10mm, .38 super, etc.) one only needed to change the barrel, recoil spring and magazine and you would use the same slide. The slide to frame fit is on par with among the best custom gun makers. Comes with a case and one magazine. This gun is perfectly adaptable with other Omega pistols and ordering other calibers whether from either Peters Stahl or Springfield is possible. I accept checks and money orders,

title: For Sale:  Another Competition/3-Gun Rifle - MI SSK12 - Loaded With Extras
postcontent:
This is easily the nicest rifle you'll find on here for the money, and likely almost anywhere else one may look.  For those not familiar with the MI SSK12 Minute Man rifle, it is an AR-15 that comes with a great and very nice looking billet receiver set made by MI. Though a great rifle out of the box, I made many upgrades to better accommodate my needs for competition shooting. With the upgrades that have been made, you're buying a rifle that you would be hard pressed to further improve upon at a price less than that of the stock rifle, not to mention the $1000+ (far more with sales tax included) I have invested in the rifle through improvements and upgrades after purchasing the rifle new in October 2013
UPGRADES ARE SUMMARIZED AT THE BOTTOM OF POST WITH ADDITIONAL DETAIL PROVIDED IN THE NEXT PARAGRAPH.

Among these upgrades are a brand new 16" 1:7 twist DRD hammer forged chrome lined barrel that I had installed in place of the original barrel in early June (poor timing on my part but at the time I had no plans to move abroad).  The rifle has been taken to the range twice since installing this new barrel with roughly 100-200 rounds having been fired. The reason for switching barrels was to improve accuracy as the DRD uses polygonal rifling as well as being cold hammer forged.  The accuracy with this new barrel is easily sub-MOA, quite possibly closer to 1/2 MOA. Other upgrades include the Magpul UBR Stock, Magpul Pro Sights, a Fortis compensator/muzzle brake, and a Geissele Super Dynamic Enhanced Flat two-stage trigger with a smooth 2 lb. first stage and a crisp 1.5 lb. second stage (Note that the Geissele trigger is not pictured as it was just installed and the trigger shown in the pictures is a Timney). The rifle originally came with a shorter 13" rail, but I had this replaced with a new MI Gen 2 quad rail when the new barrel was recently installed. A Weaver 1-5x tactical scope with offset mount and a Sight Docter mini red-dot sight is also included. Another nice feature is the upgraded BCG which is a Titanium Boron (TiN) Bolt Carrier Group. You can see the gold coloring of this BCG in the photos and in addition to improving the look, this bcg is very tough due to this coating, quite easy to clean and maintain, and functions flawlessly. 

As I'm preparing to move abroad where I will not have any use for my weapons, I'm selling two rifles, including this one, and one 1911 handgun. This rifle had originally sold for just over $1600 when I purchased it last fall and the value of the aforementioned upgrades has been well over $1,000. When you factor in the sales tax, this price is quite a bargain.  The listing price of $1,550 includes the optic but I am willing to sell the rifle without the scope for $1,450.  Any offers below full price will not come with scope or triggers mentioned, but instead a JP single stage, unless otherwise negotiated.  Please let me know if you have any questions. Thanks! 

UPGRADES
-Billet Receiver Set - Not an upgrade but a very nice feature rare in even high end ARs.
-New 16" DRD Cold Hammer Forged Chrome Lined Barrel with Polygonal Rifling
-Magpul UBR Stock
-Magpul Pro Backup Sights
-Fortis Compensator/Muzzle Brake
-Geissele Super Dynamic Enhanced Flat Two-Stage Trigger - Total 3lb. pull
-Timney 3 lb. Adjustable Single-Stage Trigger is pictured but no longer installed
-Replaced the stock 13" circular rail with a Gen 2 15" Quad Rail by MI
-Upgraded BCG to a Titanium Boron (TiN) Bolt Carrier Group - Looks great with the gold 
      shine and is much harder to prevent damage and make cleaning very easy.
-Optic is a Weaver 1-5x tactical scope with offset mount and a Sight Docter mini red-dot.
